<p>Hi everyone, welcome to my new, shiny, <a href="https://quarto.org/">quarto</a>-based web-site.</p>
<p>Before that, I was using Jekyll, as recommended by the <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/pages">github pages</a> documentation. However, Jekyll is really overkill for a simple academic website (and a simpleton like myself). I tried different things, and ended up using this <a href="https://academicpages.github.io/">template</a>, but I found it difficult to adapt to my needs (and itâ€™s not maintained anymore).</p>
<p>Long story short: I have just switched to <a href="https://quarto.org/">quarto</a>, and I am very glad I did. I manage to do more advanced things (like adding a blog) in much less time.</p>
<p>Also, math support is great: <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?2+%5Cint_0%5E1%20f(x)%20dx">. You can also type code:</p>
